<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="28" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1437,151,429]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,260,285]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Remarks.</emphasis>
This new species differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1966" box="[672,833,260,284]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="antiguensis">
<emphasis box="[672,833,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">A. antiguensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having the body black; the mandible narrow; the clypeus angulate and long; the eye small; the ocelli small; and the pronotal disc without a transverse pronotal carina, whereas 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1966" box="[332,492,332,356]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="antiguensis">
<emphasis box="[332,492,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">A. antiguensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the body with green reflection; the mandible wide, slightly angled, and with the lower tooth longer than others; the clypeus with the median lobe angulate and short; the eye large; the ocelli very small; and the pronotal disc with a transverse pronotal carina.
</paragraph>
